runs.comm: floats one up outside off stump, defended to the off side
length ball, no much turn, Swart strides down and gets a single towards mid on

big shout and gone! Only Utseya seemed to be appealing, and Myburgh seems a little surprised. The batsman definitely hit the ball, but it might have brushed pad first. Utseya comes around the stumps and gets one to straighten on about middle stump. Goes up in appeal despite a distinct woody sound, and the umpire gives him.
floated up on off stump, and Barresi eases into an off drive, sending it all along the ground to the straight boundary
closer in to the stumps this time, and a little shorter. Defended
length ball turning slightly in towards the batsman. Barresi defends again
short of a length a little wide outside off. Punched to point.
Swart comes down the pitch and gets it to mid on again, calling his partner through quickly
he's not messing around. This one is short and wide, Barresi frees his arms and strokes it nicely through cover. Nice shot.
hits the boundary on the other side of the field now. Panyangara hasn't done much wrong, delivering length just outside off, but Barresi sets himself and lifts it over midwicket for four
and he uproots Barresi's leg stump in response. A little shuffle from the batsman, but this one comes in at him on the angle, and he lets it go between bat and pad to strike the top of the leg stump
full ball, nice shape away. Left alone.
full and flat, Swart steps down the crease again, but defends back to the bowler this time
full and flat again, big appeal as Swart misses the sweep, but that's heading down leg side
length ball, turning towards leg. Hit aerially towards midwicket, but it's into space

this is swept in the air towards short fine leg, and there's some confusion over whether Panyangara has caught it on the full. No one seems that excited, and on first look, it looked like it bounced just in front. Fielder says he's not sure, and the decision goes upstairs. Looks like it hit the ground just as he got his fingers around it, so it's not out. Could have dived forward to take it on the full, though.
full on middle stump, driven back to the bowler
sweep again, but this time he connects well enough to get it over short fine leg. Bounces away to the fence

brainless from Netherlands, when they needed to rebuild. Swart bunts it and takes off tenatatively for a run, but Chatara is on to it like a flash. Sprints down the pitch collects the ball and underarms it to the stumps before Swart can turn around and head back
luck first ball. He tries to cut a widish short ball and gets an under edge, sending it past the keeper
shortish ball on off stump, defended into the off side
short-of-a-length again, and it's defended solidly
terrific timing on that one. It was just a gentle punch, but Cooper gets it past the infield through the covers, thanks in part to sloppy fielding
appeal as Cooper is stuck on the knee roll, advancing, but I think that hit him outside the off stump line

sloppy, fielding again on the fence. Borren hoicked this between deep midwicket and deep square leg, but although the fielders make the ground easily, a misfield on the fence allows the ball to get through to the rope
more sloppy work. Borren shapes for a reverse sweep but misses. Utseya fires it down what would have been the leg side, but it evades Brendan Taylor and dribbles away to the fine leg boundary
what drama this is! Borren throws it away now. Thats bowled flat on middle stump, and Borren tries to lift it straight but mishits it. Gets it down the throat of mid off
fullish, and a little slower. Defended.
full and slower again, Cooper drives this straight and the man at long off runs around to cut it off with a dive
on the legs, defended to the on side
short, wide and smashed, but Sibanda at backward point puts in a lightning dive to the left and stops four
length on the legs, Cooper tries to flay it away on the leg side but doesn't time it
slower ball, floated up. Cooper picks it and defends
short of a length, and slashed away on the off side again, but Sibanda deflects it and the man at extra cover cleans up
short and wide, cut straight to Sibanda
flatitsh, straightening on leg stump. Eased to long on for one.
fuller, floated up on off. Ben Cooper drives to long on
flat, errant legside delivery, and Tom Cooper misses out. Can only get it as far as short-fine leg
fired down off side, that's wide
this one's a bit straighter, but still not doing anything off the surface, worked into leg for one
that deserved punishment. Long hop on leg stump, easily dispatched to the square leg boundary
flat again, but it's hit straight for one
floated up on off stump, driven straight for a single
nicely flighted again, Ben Cooper drives to long on
pulls the length back a bit, and the batsman hits back to the bowler
bit quicker length ball, driven on the up to long on
more runs down the ground. This is hit past the bowler and long on comes around to clean up
length ball on the legs, Tom Cooper goes back and drives it to long on again
full and on off stump, pushed through. Driven to long on.
length ball on the stumps, swept along the ground to deep square leg
pushed through quickly again, Cooper goes back and punches, but can't beat the infield
hint of a long hop, but Tom Cooper doesn't cash in. Just hits it along the ground to deep square leg
this is fired flat and wide of off stump, Ben tries to cut but doesn't get bat on it
that's way down leg side. Taylor does well to collect
tossed up on the toes, driven to long on
flattish but pitched up, driven to long off
these guys are loving that 'V'. Another single down the ground off a full one
length on the stumps, hit to midwicket
length ball, again on off stump, worked to off for a single
lengh on the pads, Tom goes on the back foot to get it wide of long on
length on the stumps, can't beat the infield
flat  but full, Cooper tries to force it through the off side but it's fielded in the covers
floated up wide of off stump, Tom Cooper reaches out and drags it to long on
poor ball, way down leg. Ben Cooper sweeps but short fine leg does well to stop it
this is a little to full to pull, but Cooper gets it as far as deep midwicket
fired in flatter, hit in to the leg side, but there's no single
this is pitched wide of off stump and it's short enough to cut. Ben Cooper hits it out to the offside sweeper.
floaty length ball on the legs, and Ben Cooper just tickles it away fine of short-fine leg. Easy pickings.
this is wider outside the off stump, chopped to point
floated up and straightening on middle stump, batsman comes forward and turns it to deep midwicket
floated and straightening on middle again, Tom Cooper turns it gently onto the leg side and there's a big enough space on that side of the field to scramble two
length ball, flatter this time. Punched down to long on
poor ball, poor shot, but just a single. That's short and turning down leg side, but the batsman is way to early on the shot and it strikes him on the glove to lob over the keeper
short of a length on off stump, punched away past the covers
that one surprised Tom Cooper. Shortish ball on off stump, it came back off the seam and hit the batsman's glove
floated up way wide of off stump
length ball on off stump, hit to long on off the back stump. That shot has been productive for Tom Cooper.
full and on the stumps, Ben sweeps and gets it past the infield but the deep square leg cuts it off
whack! That's a floater again, overpitched about a foot outside the off stump. Tom Cooper takes aim and slaps it over long off for six
tries the shot again, but Masakadza has pulled back the length, and the batsman hits on the bounce to long off
flat on the pads, Tom tries to swat it away on the leg side but can't manage
shorter in length, pushed through. Tom hits it straight to cover
gets him away finally. This is full and straightening on the stumps, Tom sweeps it square of the short fine leg
Ben Cooper goes trying to force the pace. That was pushed through and straightening on the stumps as well. Cooper lifts it straight but doesn't connect well. Man at long on fence takes an easy catch
worsens his figures slightly with a short, wide one. Cooper cuts it between backward point and short third man. Maybe that could have been stopped.
full and on the stumps, whipped straight to short midwicket
floated up on the toes, driven to long on
a floaty length ball, turning away. This is punched down to long off
length ball straightening on the stumps, worked square on the leg side
length, turning away outside off. Punched to cover
this is fuller on off stump, driven to long off
length ball on the pads, whipped away straight of deep midwicket. It was a tight second run, but he's safe. A direct hit might have been a different story.
length again, on middle stump. Cooper turns it behind square on the leg side, but can't get it beyond the short fine leg
length ball wide of off stump, takes a thick outside edge and there's a single to third man
full and fired six inches down the leg side
full outside off stump, Cooper whips that to midwicket again. Doesn't try a second run this time
slower ball, length outside off stump. Bukhari chops it towards cover and sets off
full outside off stump again, jams down on that and gets into long on
poor ball to start. Fires it full and way down leg, Cooper paddles it fine to complete a fine, fifty. Netherlands needed that.
full on the legs again, swept square this time, to deep square leg
length ball turning into the batsman, who can't get bat to it. There's a shout, but that's going down leg
fullish ball, punched to long on
full again on the pads. Cooper sweeps it to square leg again, all along the ground
fired full and fast on the toes, Bukhari hits it to long on
good yorker to start, rigth in the blockhole, Bukhari jams down on it and gets it into space on the legside

more poor fielding. This has cost Zimbabwe a lot of runs in this innings. Cooper hits a full ball down the ground, but the man running around from long on basically helps it on to the fence, with a slide
misses his line and Cooper punishes him. This is full outside leg stump, Cooper helps it along to the long leg fence.
super shot. Clipped off the toes with immense power. Deep square leg doesn't have a great distance to cover, but it goes to the fence straight of him
tries the scoop shot off a length ball, but he can't connect
floated up wide of off stump, Cooper frees his arms, but finds the man at point
shortish ball outside off stump, Bukhari chops it square on the off side
nutmegs him with a yorker. That was full, going just down the leg side, but Cooper gets one leg either side and it goes through the gap
shortish slower ball, angled into the body. Cooper tries to pull but it hits him on the stomach. Batsmen scamper through
length ball on the stumps, Bukhari is trying to whack it, but connects only well enough to get a single to long on
decent yorker again, turned towards deepmidwicket

a good throw would have ended Bukhari's innings. Bukhari swats it away to the legside and turns for the second, but although the batsman is struggling, Taylor has too much work to do, His underarm throw misses the stumps.
full ball on the pads, Cooper can't get bat to it, but the leg bye is on offer
full ball again. Bukhari makes room to try hit through off, but can only get it back to the bowler
yorker again, Bukhari makes room once more and swings. An inside edge gets him one.

what do you call that? This is a switch-hit reverse scoop, I think. It was a slow bouncer from Panyangara. Cooper switches his stance and grip, then scoops it over what should have been short third man. Super innovation. Bounces inches inside the rope.
yorker, Cooper tries a similar shot but the length isn't there for him. They take one as this dribbles square on the off side
full ball, Bukhari does his usual grand swing, and as per usual, gets just enough bat on it to get it to long on
